-- 
INTRODUCTION
--

Nitrogen-mode is a major Emacs mode, derived from erlang-mode, that
fixes Erlang indentation to be more nitrogen friendly by indenting
block at a fixed amount rather than underneath the end of the block.

In other words, it changes this:

    Elements = #panel { body=[
                              #span { text="Hello, World!" }
                             ]}

Into this:

    Elements = #panel { body=[
        #span { text="Hello, World!" }
    ]},


--
INSTALLATION
--

To install, add nitrogen-mode.el to your load path, and then run:

(require 'nitrogen-mode)
